&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Botswana&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The pula is the currency of &lt;strong&gt;Botswana&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Pula literally means &amp;quot;rain&amp;quot; in Setswana, because rain is very scarce in Botswana.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (51, 51, 51);   letter-spacing: 0.1px;&quot;&gt;Botswana is a &lt;strong&gt;landlocked &lt;/strong&gt;country in southern Africa. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (51, 51, 51);   letter-spacing: 0.1px;&quot;&gt;It is bordered by&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;-webkit-tap-highlight-color:  a(0, 0, 0, 0);  line-height: 1.5; background-image: linear-gradient(120deg,  (255, 204, 0),  (255, 204, 0)); background-position: 0px 100%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-left: none; border-image: initial; border-bottom: 2px solid  (255, 204, 0);   transition: background-size 0.125s ease-in 0s; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; letter-spacing: 0.1px; outline: 0px;&quot;&gt;South Africa&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (51, 51, 51);   letter-spacing: 0.1px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;to the south and east, by Namibia to the west, and by Zimbabwe to the east.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (51, 51, 51);   letter-spacing: 0.1px;&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;massive Kalahari Desert &lt;/strong&gt;covers more than 70 percent of Botswana.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (51, 51, 51);   letter-spacing: 0.1px;&quot;&gt;Most of the country is covered by&lt;strong&gt; grassland called savanna.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Bengaluru&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; &quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Rail Wheel Factory was&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;formerly known as Wheel and Axle Plant is situated in&amp;nbsp; Bangalore, Karnataka.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a state-of-the-art plant, meeting the bulk of the requirement of wheels, axles and wheelsets for the Indian Railways.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;The spare capacity available is profitably utilised to meet the domestic demands for non-railway customers and exports.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;RWF has implemented ISO 14001 Environment Management system standard during 1996&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;again first PU in Indian Railways to implement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RWF has&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;become the first PU in Indian Railways to Integrate ISO 9001, 14001 &amp;amp; OHSAS 18001&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;system standard during&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;2013.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; &quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first railway on the Indian sub-continent ran over a stretch of 21 miles from Bombay to Thane.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The idea of a railway to connect&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Bombay with Thane, Kalyan and with the Thal and Bhore Ghats&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;inclines&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;first occurred to Mr George Clark in 1843.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first formal inauguration ceremony was performed in 1853.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;South, the first line was opened in 1856.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;India has&amp;nbsp;8 Railway Museums in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Delhi, Pune, Kanpur, Mysore, Kolkata, Chennai, Ghum and Tiruchirappalli.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The railway budget was separated from the general budget in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;1924.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kolkata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Metro Railway, Kolkata is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first underground Metro&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Metro services in Kolkata began on&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;24 October 1984.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It ran between&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Esplanade and Bhowanipur&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(currently Netaji Bhavan) covering a distance of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;3.40 km.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The first metro was driven by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Tapan Kumar Nath and Sanjoy Sil.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The foundation stone of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Kolkata Metro&amp;nbsp;project&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;was laid by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indira Gandhi&lt;/span&gt;, on&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;29 December 1972,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and construction work started in 1973&amp;ndash;74.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Physical construction work on the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Delhi Metro&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;started on&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;1 October 1998.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assam.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Assam&amp;nbsp;is known as the&lt;strong&gt; land of the Red River and Blue Hills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Assam is referred so as the &lt;b&gt;Red River &lt;/b&gt;refers to the &lt;b&gt;river Brahmaputra,&lt;/b&gt; and the&lt;b&gt; blue hills&lt;/b&gt; refer to the hills that shine at a distance forming a &lt;b&gt;blue cloud.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 5px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Assam is a state in &lt;b&gt;Northeast &lt;/b&gt;India, situated south of the eastern Himalayas along the&lt;b&gt; Brahmaputra and Barak &lt;/b&gt;River valleys.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Assam covers an area of &lt;b&gt;78,438 km&amp;sup2;&lt;/b&gt; (30,285 sq mi).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to Area, the Indian State Assam ranked &lt;b&gt;16th &lt;/b&gt;in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Guwahati &lt;/b&gt;is the largest metropolitan area and urban conglomeration in Assam, administered under the highest form of the local urban body-Guwahati Municipal Corporation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The state is bounded to the north by &lt;b&gt;Bhutan and Arunachal Pradesh&lt;/b&gt;; to the east by&lt;b&gt; Nagaland and Manipur&lt;/b&gt;; to the south by &lt;b&gt;Meghalaya&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;Tripura&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;Mizoram&lt;/b&gt;, and &lt;b&gt;Bangladesh&lt;/b&gt;; and to the west by the Siliguri Corridor by &lt;b&gt;West Bengal&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Both 1 &amp;amp; 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

